HEADWORD: Unbarbed
<hw>Un*barbed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
shaven.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of barbs, or of reversed points, hairs, or
plumes; <as>as, an <ex>unbarbed</ex> feather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbark</ent>⟦br⟧
